I set the Da, Db, F, and K variables to be controls in Tweakpane. I tried to explore the flow option, but ended up doing something different that fulfilled the requirement.
I added a flow function to my compute shader that returns an augmented vec2f based on the pixel's x and y coords. Specifically, it returns the vec2f(sin(y*2)+1, cos(x*2)).
I then use this vector to offset where the laplace is being calculated, and treat the rest of the reaction diffusion calcuations the same. So the simulation is calculating
The Laplace function on a position that is offset by the flow function instead of the pixel's true position. I really wanted to make a water or river effect, and this ended
up doing exactly what I wanted, albeit in a way that I didn't fully intend. The flow function also adds some black rectangles on the screen that the pixels seem to flow
around, which is a really cool effect, and I'm not entirely sure why those rectangles exist.

